          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 5: Industry Operations (light) -->
<section style="background:#F8F6F1;padding:5rem 0;">
  <div style="max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:660px;margin:0 auto 2rem;text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(1.6rem,3.5vw,2.4rem);color:#0A0A0A;margin-bottom:1rem;">Industry Operations</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.9375rem;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(10,10,10,0.55);">Generic automation advice misses the specific operational patterns of each industry. A property manager handling 200 units has entirely different workflow requirements than a restaurant managing online orders. A construction company winning bids needs different automation than a gym managing member journeys. These guides go deep into each vertical.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(300px,1fr));gap:1.25rem;">
      {[
        { slug: 'property-management-automation-tenant-landlord-workflows-2026', title: 'Property Management Automation: How to Run 200 Units Without a Full Ops Team', excerpt: 'Property managers handling 200 units with a small team are drowning in maintenance requests, tenant communications, rent collection, and compliance checks.', tags: ['property','real estate','tenants'] },
        { slug: 'restaurant-automation-orders-staff-reviews-2026', title: 'Restaurant Automation: From Online Orders to Staff Scheduling on Autopilot', excerpt: 'Restaurants operating on 3-5% net margins cannot afford the hidden costs of manual operations: missed orders, scheduling errors, and lost reviews.', tags: ['restaurant','hospitality','scheduling'] },
        { slug: 'construction-company-automation-project-workflows-2026', title: 'Construction Company Automation: Project Management Workflows That Win More Jobs', excerpt: 'Construction companies lose bids because quotes take too long. They lose margin because site communications are inefficient. Automation fixes both.', tags: ['construction','project management','quotes'] },
        { slug: 'gym-fitness-studio-automation-member-workflows-2026', title: 'Gym and Fitness Studio Automation: Member Journeys That Run Without You', excerpt: 'Gym owners and studio managers spend 60% of their operational time on tasks that should be automated: new member onboarding, class reminders, payment chasing.', tags: ['gym','fitness','members'] },
        { slug: 'nonprofit-automation-donor-volunteer-management-2026', title: 'Nonprofit Automation: How Charities Are Doing More With Less Using Workflows', excerpt: 'Charities face the same operational complexity as businesses but with a fraction of the budget and staff. Automation closes that gap significantly.', tags: ['nonprofit','charity','donors'] },
